org.chronos.common.builder

Interface ChronoBuilder<SELF extends ChronoBuilder<?>>

  • Type Parameters:
    SELF - The dynamic type of this to return for method chaining.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractChronoBuilder

    public interface ChronoBuilder<SELF extends ChronoBuilder<?>>
    A generic builder interface that allows setting properties as key-value pairs.

        SELF withProperty(java.lang.String key,
                  java.lang.String value)

        Parameters:
        key - The key to set. Must not be null.
        value - The value to set. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        this (for fluent method chaining).

      • withPropertiesFile

        SELF withPropertiesFile(java.io.File file)
        Loads the given properties file as configuration for this builder.

        The file must fulfill all of the following conditions:

        • The file must be a file, not a directory.
        • The file must exist.
        • The file must be accessible.
        • The file name must end with .properties
        • The file contents must follow the default Properties format.
        Parameters:
        file - The properties file to read. Must not be null, must adhere to all of the conditions stated above.
        Returns:
        this (for fluent method chaining).

      • withPropertiesFile

        SELF withPropertiesFile(java.lang.String filePath)
        Loads the properties file via the given path as configuration for this builder.

        The file given by the path must fulfill all of the following conditions:

        • The file must be a file, not a directory.
        • The file must exist.
        • The file must be accessible.
        • The file name must end with .properties
        • The file contents must follow the default Properties format.
        Parameters:
        filePath - The file path to the properties file to read. Must not be null, must adhere to all of the conditions stated above.
        Returns:
        this (for fluent method chaining).
